name: Duck Carnitas Tacos With Radish Escab√®che

steps.instruction:
Made by [Rick Martinez](https://www.bonappetit.com/recipe/duck-carnitas-tacos-with-radish-escabeche)

### Prep
- Cut the Morita Chiles in half lengthwise
- Cut the navel orange into quarters
- Cut the head of garlic in half crosswise
- Trim the radishes, cut it in half, thinly slice
- Slice the white onion thinly
- Tear the mint leaves
- Tear the Tarragon Leaves
- Thinly slice the fresno chiles

### Duck
1. Prick skin on duck legs in several places with the tip of a paring knife
2. Rub legs with salt, working into flesh and skin
3. Transfer to a medium bowl or airtight container
4. Cover and chill at least 12 hours and up to 1 day.

5. Place a rack in middle of oven; preheat to 250¬∞
6. Heat lard in a large saucepan over medium-high until an instant-read thermometer registers 250¬∞.

7. Scatter chiles, bay leaf, cinnamon stick, cloves, achiote seeds, peppercorns, and oregano across the bottom of a large baking dish
8. Remove duck legs from bowl and brush off excess salt
9. Arrange legs, skin side down, over aromatics in baking dish
10. Nestle orange and garlic around legs, then pour warm lard over.
11. Cover baking dish tightly with foil and bake legs 2 hours

12. Turn duck legs skin side up and nestle back into fat
13. Re-cover dish and continue to bake until meat is very tender and begins to pull away from the bones, 2‚Äì2¬Ω hours longer.

14. Let duck legs sit in fat until cool enough to handle (30‚Äì40 minutes), then transfer to a plate
15. Reserve 3 Tbsp. fat for frying duck skin and strain remaining fat through a fine-mesh sieve into an airtight container and let cool.
16. Cover and reserve for another use (see recipe intro for ideas!).

17. Remove skin from legs and set aside
18. Pull meat from bones, tearing into 1" pieces; discard bones and cartilage
19. Heat reserved 3 Tbsp. fat in a large nonstick skillet over medium and cook reserved duck skin, turning halfway through, until deep golden brown and crisp on both sides, 12‚Äì15 minutes total
20. Transfer chicharrones to paper towels to drain and let cool 5 minutes; crumble into small pieces.

#### Do Ahead:
- Duck legs can be baked 3 weeks ahead. Transfer whole legs to a large nonreactive container; strain fat through a fine-mesh sieve over meat. Cover and chill. Bring to room temperature before removing skin and shredding meat.

### Escab√®che and Assembly
21. Whisk lime juice, honey, and salt in a medium bowl until salt and honey are dissolved
22. Add radishes, onion, mint, tarragon, and 1 chile and toss to coat.
23. Add remaining chiles as desired (depending on their heat and how spicy you like things).
24. Top warm tortillas with some reserved meat, then radish escab√®che and reserved chicharrones.
